{"type":"text","timestamp":1781083034825,"sessionID":"ses_14f2f6605ffeEk11ACiTpW64NC","part":{"id":"prt_eb0d22a50001dMHI584sLE0YLI","messageID":"msg_eb0d2251a001xBtJCF0DmNac1t","sessionID":"ses_14f2f6605ffeEk11ACiTpW64NC","type":"text","text":"No .dockerignore exists. The Harbor docs mention it. Not a blocker but worth noting.\n\nNow let me analyze test.sh sections critically:\n\nLooking at test.sh, considering hardened isolation (agent=non-root, /tests=700, strace wrap):\n\n**Useful sections:**\n- `chmod 700 /logs/verifier` + `rm -rf` (mandatory)\n- `chmod 700 /tests` re-lock (Harbor reset risk — useful)\n- Oracle decryption + ELF validation\n- Build under strace as agent + env -i\n- run_all.py with strace per case\n- Reward-tamper tripwire \n- Static workspace anti-cheat greps (useful — specific to this task: oracle path, decryption key, banned crates, identical binary check)\n- compute_reward.py call outside strace\n\n**Potentially redundant:**\n- `unset LD_PRELOAD LD_LIBRARY_PATH PYTHONPATH PYTHONHOME BASH_ENV ENV CARGO_HOME...`: agent is non-root, so cannot write to `/etc/ld.so.preload`. But agent CAN set its own env vars that leak into test.sh inheritance if test.sh inherits from prior shell — but test.sh is launched by Harbor, not the agent. These env vars would have to be planted via `~/.bashrc` for `bash -lc`. Mostly defensive but reasonable.\n- `pkill -9 -u agent` + retry — useful: agent processes are reparented to PID 1 and can survive.\n- `find /tests -type f -name '*.sh' -exec chmod +x {} +` — comment says it's for Modal/Daytona; but no other .sh in /tests besides test.sh itself which has no helpers, so this may be a no-op. Let me verify.","time":{"start":1781083023952,"end":1781083034817}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1781083036760,"sessionID":"ses_14f2f6605ffeEk11ACiTpW64NC","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"bash","callID":"toolu_012mE8etp62X1cWshcVSJSCx","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"command":"grep -n \"\\.sh\\b\" tests/test.sh tests/run_all.py 2>/dev/null | grep -v \"^.*#\" | head -10; echo \"---\"; ls environment/tests/ 2>/dev/null || echo \"no environment/tests\"","description":"Look for other .sh files referenced","workdir":"/Users/dheeraj/Downloads/refactor/bespoke-labs-tasks-01/rust-ls-color-advanced"},"output":"tests/test.sh:71:find /tests -type f -name '*.sh' -exec chmod +x {} + 2>/dev/null || true\ntests/run_all.py:2:\"\"\"rust-ls Phase-1 executor (runs as ROOT, invoked by tests/test.sh).\ntests/run_all.py:23:    WORK_DIR/cheat.txt and aborts; test.sh turns that into a zero-with-cheat.\n---\nno environment/tests\n","metadata":{"output":"tests/test.sh:71:find /tests -type f -name '*.sh' -exec chmod +x {} + 2>/dev/null || true\ntests/run_all.py:2:\"\"\"rust-ls Phase-1 executor (runs as ROOT, invoked by tests/test.sh).\ntests/run_all.py:23:    WORK_DIR/cheat.txt and aborts; test.sh turns that into a zero-with-cheat.\n---\nno environment/tests\n","exit":0,"description":"Look for other .sh files referenced","truncated":false},"title":"Look for other .sh files referenced","time":{"start":1781083036753,"end":1781083036758}},"metadata":{"anthropic":{"caller":{"type":"direct"}}},"id":"prt_eb0d254c50018t9JMc76dDcHwT","sessionID":"ses_14f2f6605ffeEk11ACiTpW64NC","messageID":"msg_eb0d2251a001xBtJCF0DmNac1t"}}
